{"word":"Amalekites","slug":"amalekites","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Amalekites</b> A people inhabiting the country south of Idumea and east of the Red Sea<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=13&verse=29'>Num 13:29</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=14&verse=25'>Num 14:25</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=15&verse=7'>1Sa 15:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=27&verse=8'>1Sa 27:8</a><br/> Defeated by:<br/> - Chedorlaomer<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=14&verse=7'>Gen 14:7</a> <br/> - Joshua<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=17&verse=8'>Exo 17:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=17&verse=13'>Exo 17:13</a> <br/> - Gideon<br/> <a href='B:'></a> <br/> - Saul<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=14&verse=48'>1Sa 14:48</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=15&verse=33'>1Sa 15:33</a> <br/> - David<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=27&verse=9'>1Sa 27:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=30&verse=20'>1Sa 30:20</a> <br/> - The Simeonites<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=4&verse=43'>1Ch 4:43</a> <br/> Defeat the Israelites<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=14&verse=45'>Num 14:45</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=3&verse=13'>Jdg 3:13</a><br/> Israel commanded to destroy<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=25&verse=19'>Deu 25:19</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=28&verse=18'>1Sa 28:18</a><br/> Prophecies against<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=17&verse=14'>Exo 17:14</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=17&verse=16'>Exo 17:16</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=24&verse=20'>Num 24:20</a>"}]}